hopobject.body: Not in at the moment revista electronica portalesmedicos.com The survey also reports that nearly three-quarters of shoppers reported reading food labels for ingredients and "other product information." Well, here's a crazy thought. Perhaps food-label reading has become a barrier in and of itself to eating more healthfully; these days, the jobs of food labels seem to be to dupe consumers into believing that boxes of heavily processed food with a vitamin or two or a few grams of whole grains are suddenly healthful choices.
